The issue is that the function is returning an object, and when you try to output an object directly, it returns "[object Object]". To fix this, you should access the specific value you want to retrieve from the object and return that value instead. Let me correct the function for you:

```javascript
function PredictCirrhosisOutcomes(N_Days, Drug, Age, Sex, Ascites, Hepatomegaly, Spiders, Edema, Bilirubin, Cholesterol, Albumin, Copper, Alk_Phos, SGOT, Tryglicerides, Platelets, Prothrombin, Stage) {
